<br>
“Got done early,” he said. He shared a look with Clark and then an expression of comprehension crossed Lana’s face.<br>
<br>
“Oh,” she said, now in understanding of the situation. Jerome furrowed his brow and looked at Clark.<br>
<br>
“Does she know?” He asked. Clark nodded.<br>
<br>
“Yeah, but don’t worry, she won’t tell anybody,” Clark said. Lana smiled up at him. He trusted her. It was such a nice feeling, and she hadn’t gotten used to it yet. Jerome grinned and crossed his arms.<br>
<br>
“I guess if you trust her, then I can too,” Jerome said. Lana turned to face him. He was still glistening, but she figured that had more to do with the heat that had fallen upon them rather than the work he had been doing. He looked so good, and she suddenly wondered why she hadn’t taken advantage of her many opportunities to ogle Clark when he was doing farm work.<br>
<br>
