<br>
“Chloe?” He asked.<br>
<br>
“I can’t do this,” Chloe said in a weepy tone. “I’m sorry. I know in your mind that we’re married and everything’s probably great, but I don’t remember being married to you. You’re my friend and ---”<br>
<br>
“Your friend who you dream about,” he murmured in her ear. He didn’t see the tears starting to well up in her eyes.<br>
<br>
