<br>
‘Think of something,’ he told himself. An evil smile crept across his lips, but he managed to pull off an apologetic look when he turned around to face her. “I think it might be my fault,” he said. Chloe creased her brow.<br>
<br>
“What?” She asked. Clark walked back over to the bed and sat down.<br>
<br>
“I brought you back some food this morning and I didn’t know you were right behind the bathroom door and,”<br>
<br>
“And it slammed into me,” Chloe finished.<br>
<br>
